result.name: Ngong Ping Garden Restaurant

reviews.text:
Food is stuff I can make at home as a college student. 

Ordered shrimp wonton soup, and the broth still contained the powder for the broth. They brought out what appeared to be complimentary peanuts and tea as usual, but it showed up on the bill without warning which may be problematic to some.

They have an excessive number of staff that stand around and uncomfortably stare you down as you eat. 

⭐Hidden, included 10% service charge with any meal
Overpriced, poor quality. Tourist trap!! Not as many vegetarian options as it claims, the food was plain, and it was rather expensive

Just horrid.  Massively overpriced and every dish was either disappointing or disgusting.  My beef dish had two tiny morsels of beef and a wad of fat and gristle that would choke a horse.  The king pao chicken was 97% celery. The seafood soup had fake crab and not much else, including taste.  Did I mention it was overpriced?

Awful experience. Went for vegetarian as the menu seemed extensive. Not much was actually available to choose from. They bought out the wrong meal - with meat in it! Sent it back, got my proper meal after a long time... Plain, zero taste. Was like they boiled the vermicelli and served in the same water. Basically ate noodles and water. 1 price of green veg and a couple of mushrooms. The soup and noodles themselves however could have fed 7 people.. I was alone. Left more than half the dish remaining. Over priced and sneaky 10% charge on top. Shouldn't have paid a thing due to wrong meal AND horrible one.. not happy with it. AVOID.

Surprisingly we went there on a public holiday, all the other restaurants were jam packed but this place was fairly vacant! So we went in and gave it a try. It wasn’t cheap, but at such touristy location I reckon it is still acceptable. Food tasted nice, everything were nicely made. We would come again.
